Information
------------------------------

My Tattoo Addiction: Series 2
My Tattoo Addiction returns for a new three-part series, revisiting the captivating world of tattoos and exploring more of the unique stories behind every tattoo design. In the tattoo world you can either stand out or fit in. This episode meets the individuals whose tattoos make them feel whole and make a statement about the person they want to be. Unemployed father-of-six Paul's facial tattoos are his pride and joy but are also a barrier to regular work. Duncan expresses his grief at the loss of a close friend through the ink on his body, while James expresses his desire to escape from his surroundings in his tattoos. And Helen and Amy's tattoos are part of their attempt to fit in to a world that views them as outsiders. The documentary takes viewers into the lives of the people who get tattoos, exploring their motives and experiences while asking why, as a country, we're addicted to tattoos.


1)  Part 1 
This episode meets people whose body art represents their way of moving on, from Cathy, whose obsession with a certain novel helped her come to terms with a difficult past, to Lindsey, who is getting her first tattoo in her 40s to celebrate the most important person in her life, and Dave, who hopes his new tattoo will cover the scars of a failed relationship. Featuring eye-watering footage and intimate interviews, the programme takes viewers into the lives of people who get tattoos, exploring their motives and experiences while asking why, as a country, we're so addicted to tattoos.

2)  Part 2 
Whether it's a conscious decision or a thoughtless impulse, every tattoo is a statement of someone's hopes, ambitions or state of mind. This episode meets people whose addiction to body art has had a profound effect on the way they live their lives, whether it's a manifesto or an embarrassment.

3)  Part 3 
This episode meets people whose body art represents their way of moving on. Cathy's obsession with a certain novel helped her come to terms with a difficult past. Lindsey is getting her first tattoo in her 40s to celebrate the most important person in her life. And Dave hopes his new tattoo will cover the scars of a failed relationship.

